node.text: Videos showing people smuggling migrants past Border Patrol checkpoints and flashing thousands of dollars in cash are being posted on TikTok, Texas State Troopers say. CNN's @rosaflorescnn reports.

node.title: Mexican cartels are recruiting teens on TikTok to smuggle migrants

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '98% of US residents live in an area with a "high" or "substantial" risk of Covid-19 community transmission Source: The US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention CNN'.

node.text:
More than 98% of US residents now live in an area where there is a “high” or “substantial” risk of Covid-19 community transmission, up from 19% of residents only a month ago. This sharp turn has been driven in large part by the highly infectious Delta variant and low vaccination rates in many regions.⁠
⁠
The US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention measures community transmission using two metrics — the number of cases per 100,000 people and the test positivity rate, both measured over the previous seven days.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 12, 2021. May be art of 1 person and text that says '11 Picasso paintings that could be worth up to $100 million to be auctioned in Las Vegas CNN'.

node.text:
Eleven Pablo Picasso artworks that were on display at a Las Vegas restaurant for over 20 years will hit the auction block this October, just two days before what would have been the artist's 140th birthday. Part of MGM Resorts' sizable art collection, the pieces had long been a fixture at Picasso, a Michelin-starred French and Spanish eatery in the Bellagio that is inspired by its namesake's life and work. The collection -- which includes paintings, works on paper and one ceramic work -- has a combined top estimate of $104.2 million, according to Sotheby's auction house, which is organizing the sale. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.⁠
⁠
(📸: Courtesy Sotheby's and MGM Resorts)

node.text:
With the spread of the more dangerous and transmissible Delta variant as well as lagging vaccination rates, states such as Texas are in the midst of a surge in Covid-19 cases that quickly halted a summer of reopenings. As Texas faces another rise in hospitalizations, officials are concerned over health care worker shortages. Texas Gov. Greg Abbott announced that more than 2,500 medical personnel will be deployed to hospitals around the state to care for an increasing number of Covid-19 patients. Tap the link in our bio to learn more about the surge in Texas.⁠
⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'US Intelligence assessments warn that the capital of Afghanistan could be cut off and collapse under the Taliban in the coming months CNN'.

node.text: Kabul could be isolated by the Taliban in the next 30 to 60 days, increasing the potential that the Afghan capital could fall under the control of the militant group, according to a senior administration official familiar with one US intelligence assessment. This collapse would represent a stunning defeat after the United States' costly two-decade military campaign in Afghanistan.

May be an image of 3 people and text that says 'Judge allows defamation lawsuits against Sidney Powell, Rudy Giuliani and MyPillow CEO Dominion Voting Systems is seeking billions of dollars in damages, claiming it was harmed by the unfounded claims of election fraud made by the confidants of Donald Trump. node.text:
Three major defamation lawsuits from Dominion Voting Systems against MyPillow CEO Mike Lindell and the right-wing lawyers Sidney Powell and Rudy Giuliani will move forward toward a trial, a federal judge ruled on Wednesday. The company provides election equipment used by more than 40% of US voters and claims it was harmed by the unfounded claims of election fraud made by the confidants of former President Donald Trump.⁠
⁠
(📸: Getty Images)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Under new policy, ICE will avoid arrest and deportation of undocumented victims of crime CNN'.

node.text: Immigration and Customs Enforcement will avoid arresting or deporting undocumented immigrants who are victims of crime, except in exceptional circumstances, according to a new directive. Going forward, ICE will require agents and officers to help undocumented victims seek justice and facilitate access to immigration benefits, according to the agency. The policy, issued Wednesday, marks the latest effort by the Biden administration to pivot from the Trump administration and tailor enforcement priorities. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.⁠

Ron DeSantis accused Biden of having a "wide open southern border" which led to the latest surge of Covid-19 Public health experts say there is no evidence that migrants are to blame for the spike in Covid-19 cases in Florida or other southern states. Instead, experts say the Delta variant and low vaccination rates are the primary causes of this latest wave. CNN Facts First'.

node.text: While Covid-19 continues to spike in southern states with lower vaccination rates, Republicans have tried pinning blame for the rise in cases, hospitalizations and deaths on illegal immigration and President Biden's policies at the southern border. While migrants continue to arrive at the US-Mexico border in record numbers, it's false to claim that the border is "open" as Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis did last week. The Biden administration is still using a Trump-era policy which allows for many migrants to be quickly expelled from the US.⁠

node.text: The disruption to children's routines due to the pandemic has taken a toll on their mental health, new analysis suggests. "Results from this analysis suggest that the pandemic has likely instigated a global mental health crisis in youth," said study author Sheri Madigan, an associate professor of clinical psychology at the University of Calgary.

node.text: California Gov. Gavin Newsom announced Wednesday that teachers and other school employees must either show proof of full vaccination or be tested at least once a week. The order will take effect Thursday and schools must be in full compliance by October 15, according to the statement.⁠
